Comment: E.A.Silverstein,S.R.Salisbury,G.Hardie and L.D.Oppliger
      Phys.Rev. 124 (1961) 868;
     Thin(~2 keV) gas  targets  have  been  used  for  14N(a,a)14N
differential cross sections for 1.0-2.4 MeV. Data  were  taken  at
five angles (169 deg 58', 140 deg 46', 125 deg 16', 90 deg, 54 deg
44' c.m.). Resonances were observed  at  Ea=1.533,  1.620,  2.165,
2.351,  2.370  MeV.  Also  16O(3He,3He)16O   and   16O(3He,4He)15O
differential cross sections were measured  for  energy  range  1-3
MeV. The systematic cross section uncertainties  is  estimated  by
authors to be 1.3% in the worst  case.  Only  graphical  data  are
presented.
The data were converted c.m. -> lab.
